Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.45,0:00:17.76,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,After Cao Cao accepted Guan Yu's three conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.28,0:00:19.85,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,Guan Yu missed Liu Bei on one side
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.85,0:00:23.16,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,and took care of Ladies Gan and Mi on the other
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.32,0:00:26.78,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,whilst following Cao Cao to Xudu.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.52,0:00:32.60,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,Liu Bei lost Xiaopei, Xu Province, Xiapi in rapid succession
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.70,0:00:35.08,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,and had no choice but to join Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.76,0:00:40.83,Default,Narrator,0,0,0,,Zhang Fei broke out of a heavy siege and left towards Mount Mangdang.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.73,0:00:48.65,Default,GuanYu,0,0,0,,Sisters-in-law, you must be exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.65,0:00:52.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,However, we still need to travel tomorrow so please rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.98,0:00:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother-in-law, you must be exhausted as well, so please return and rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.90,0:01:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,General, please rest. We will take our leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.60,0:01:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead me to the living quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.52,0:01:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why aren't you leading me to the living quarters?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.14,0:01:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,General, some soldiers are sleeping in the streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.74,0:01:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be hard for you to escort the two ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.05,0:01:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I received the Chancellor's order.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.75,0:01:34.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,This room is just for the general and\N the two ladies, especially arranged for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.06,0:01:37.30,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(98,336)\fade(255,0,255,0,540,1820,2220)}Guān Yǔ\NStyled: Yúncháng
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.32,0:01:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Just this room? For both us and the two ladies?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.46,0:01:42.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,General, I do not know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.15,0:01:47.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,The Chancellor really did personally arrange these living quarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.41,0:02:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Does he want to ruin my name \Nand break the bond between lord and vassal?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.06,0:02:43.66,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(600,327)\fade(255,0,255,0,500,2060,2580)}Cáo Cāo \NStyled: Mèngdé
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.39,0:02:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.29,0:02:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I watched the night at thy orders,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:50.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,however, General Guan has been standing outside since this night.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.30,0:02:52.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I don't know why he won't leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.38,0:03:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You must serve the ladies well!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.41,0:03:07.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.25,0:03:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor Cao!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.71,0:03:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I noticed your war cloak is well-worn.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.92,0:03:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let this fine silk be your new one, made just for your size.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.32,0:03:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The distance to Xudu is significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.10,0:03:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For all that could trouble you on the road, I hope you will forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.20,0:04:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.48,0:04:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, come and take a good look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It fits well, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.72,0:04:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yunchang, why are you so modest?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I am not modest, it's that the old cloak was gifted to me by Imperial Uncle Liu.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.64,0:04:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Wearing it is like seeing my brother, \Nand how could I wear it over with your cloak
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.80,0:05:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}and forget my elder brother's kindness? \NThat is why it is on the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.75,0:05:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Sir, you really are righteous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.54,0:05:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.92,0:05:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.98,0:05:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yunchang, why is your mount so thin?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.32,0:05:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My body is heavy and the \Nhorse cannot bear it, thus it is thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.17,0:05:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yunchang, do you recognize this horse?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.65,0:05:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That can't possibly be Lü Bu's mount, Red Hare?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.09,0:06:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, why not ride it for me to see?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.39,0:06:36.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,This isn't good!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.32,0:06:39.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If Guan Yu gets this horse, he might escape and leave forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.60,0:06:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yunchang would not be so dishonorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.14,0:06:57.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Liu Bei's two wives are still in the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.28,0:06:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.51,0:07:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Get aside!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.38,0:07:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.39,0:07:14.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.47,0:07:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Many thanks, Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:26.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I gave you a silk cloak, yet you wouldn't kneel.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.96,0:07:31.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yet I give you a horse, \Nand now you kneel in reverence!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.41,0:07:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you value beasts over men?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.18,0:07:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, this horse can travel\N thousands of li in a day, and you gave it to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.00,0:07:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I know where my elder brother is,\N I can be with him in one day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.30,0:08:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You receive this much generosity, yet you still ponder leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.04,0:08:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, I'm very grateful for your kindness!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.54,0:08:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just that though my body is here,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.68,0:08:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,my heart yearns for Imperial\N Uncle Liu, and I am unable to forget him!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.67,0:08:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, you speak poorly!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,A man should weigh the value of all matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:33.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Lord Xuande's grace hardly can compare to the Chancellor's.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.09,0:08:36.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Sir, why must you only have the will to leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.95,0:08:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I do know the Chancellor has given me much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.42,0:08:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,but I also received the imperial \Nuncle's love. We swore to die together!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.69,0:08:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not betray that oath!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.77,0:09:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, I cannot remain here forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I will repay you, sire, then will I depart!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.75,0:09:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,If Xuande has left the world, where would you return?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.38,0:09:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,To the underworld.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.36,0:09:35.80,Thinking,,0,0,0,,This man never forgot his roots. \NYunchang is a righteous man in this world!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.54,0:09:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Generals, we shall march to Xudu!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.05,0:09:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Move away!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.62,0:09:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Return Yunchang home.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.80,0:10:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sire, after you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.78,0:10:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,After you, Xuande.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.10,0:10:11.94,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(98,331)\fade(255,0,255,0,500,1460,1820)}Liú Bèi\NStyled: Xuándé
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.94,0:10:16.38,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(599.34,329)\fade(255,0,255,0,0,2060,2420)}Yuán Shào\NStyled: Běnchū
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.04,0:10:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande, your face tells me something is amiss.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.92,0:10:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.89,0:10:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't understand why you are always aggrieved.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.56,0:10:40.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no news of my two brothers and my family are in the hands of that traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.00,0:10:47.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Above, I cannot repay my nation; \Nbelow, I cannot repay my family.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.50,0:10:51.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,How could anyone stay still and not be emotional?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have always wanted to capture Xudu. \NNow we have a growing army to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.09,0:11:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Cao Cao has treacherously deceived his lord. \NMy lord, you must punish him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.23,0:11:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,This will win over and unite the heroes all across the realm!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.65,0:11:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.24,0:11:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,when Cao Cao attacked Xu Province, Xudu \Nwas open, but Your Lordship did not advance!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.10,0:11:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Xu Province has been conquered! \NWe must not underestimate the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.30,0:11:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be better to maintain our position and wait for a chance to strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.80,0:11:53.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,My lord, Cao Cao is most treacherous.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.16,0:11:58.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,If we don't act now, you could \Nlose your prestige among the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.51,0:12:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande's words are very brilliant!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.10,0:12:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, Liu Bei's words cannot be trusted!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.45,0:12:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.89,0:12:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You belittle our strength with your tongue! Do you deem me to fail?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.22,0:12:16.58,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(600,331)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,1980,2340)}Tián Fēng\NStyled: Yuánhào
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.91,0:12:19.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord! To ignore my loyal advice is to doom our men!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.88,0:12:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The gall!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.37,0:12:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Guards, drag him down! Behead him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.84,0:12:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.90,0:12:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, if you ignore loyal advice, \Nit will be too late for regrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.65,0:12:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.30,0:12:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, while Tian Yuanhao has affronted your honor, it being quite contemptible,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.56,0:12:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill your own before mobilizing any troops\N would only harm the men's morale.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.03,0:12:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, please consider this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.17,0:13:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Imprison Tian Feng. He will remain there until after I finish this war.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.00,0:13:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, my lord, if you ignore loyal advice, \Nit will be too late for regrets!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.34,0:13:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord! My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.67,0:13:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I hereby assign Yan Liang as the vanguard and to attack Baima!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.92,0:13:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The main army shall accompany me as scheduled towards Liyang!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.12,0:13:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,As you wish!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.33,0:13:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Song Xian!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.15,0:13:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.78,0:13:54.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I've long heard you were a\N fierce general under Lü Bu.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.00,0:13:56.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Would you honor us by taking on Yan Liang?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.75,0:14:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, watch me seize Yan Liang's head!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.81,0:14:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,See my strength!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.74,0:14:22.86,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(122,331)}Yán Liáng
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.72,0:14:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What a strong general!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.36,0:14:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, Yan Liang killed my friend! \NI will risk my life to avenge him! Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.63,0:14:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yan Liang, I will send you to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.83,0:15:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Who dare challenge him?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.20,0:15:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.70,0:15:11.14,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(115,361)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,2000,2340)}Xú Huǎng\NStyled: Gōngmíng
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.02,0:15:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord! My lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.70,0:15:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.64,0:15:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sound the bells!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.58,0:16:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, I know one man able to match Yan Liang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.92,0:16:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.26,0:16:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Only Guan Yunchang.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.40,0:16:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But he stated he wouldn't leave until he repays me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.03,0:16:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If he repayed me, he would leave. \NThat's why I didn't let him join the fray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.97,0:16:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,If Liu Bei was here, he would ally with Yuan Shao.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.75,0:16:25.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Thus, if you send Yunchang to defeat Yuan Shào's army,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.02,0:16:28.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,Yuan Shao would suspect Liu Bei and kill him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.68,0:16:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If Liu Bei dies, then who will \NYunchang have to follow?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.03,0:16:43.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, send someone to Xudu and get Yunchang immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.81,0:16:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The troops of Hebei are known to be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.27,0:17:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}As I see them, they are nothing \Nbut a pack of puny hounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.64,0:17:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}That man under the commander's banner is well dressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.98,0:17:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}wielding a blade and \Nriding a horse. That is Yan Liang.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}As I see him, it is nothing short of easily taking his head.
Comment: 0,0:17:21.27,0:17:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Review above.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.98,0:17:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't be too arrogant.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.68,0:17:37.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,I may lack talent, but I can charge in, \Nseize his head, and present it to you, sire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.99,0:17:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no joking in warfare! \NYunchang, don't be reckless!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.46,0:17:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Beat the drums!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.33,0:18:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Cao Cao killed Yan Liang with Guan Yu,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and valued him more.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.10,0:18:31.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He had Emperor Xian of Han enfeoff \NGuan Yu as the Precinct-Marquis of Hanshou,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.10,0:18:31.11,Note (Potential style?),NTP,0,0,0,,Enfeoffs, or the granting of land in exchange for loyalty,\N was a popular tactic for warlords at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.19,0:18:33.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,forging a seal for him as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.78,0:18:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, my lord, our vanguard, Yan Liang, has been beheaded!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.10,0:18:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Who killed Yan Liang?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.29,0:18:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,One with a red face and a long beard! He wielded a glaive!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.03,0:18:53.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,His horse just burst through like no other!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.27,0:18:55.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,He beheaded Yan Liang, resulting in a major defeat!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.30,0:18:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this man?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.57,0:19:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Xuande's younger brother, Guan Yunchang.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.24,0:19:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.76,0:19:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He killed my favorite general!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.57,0:19:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be colluding with Cao Cao!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.71,0:19:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Guards!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.22,0:19:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.15,0:19:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! My lord, don't let one-sided words end our alliance!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.68,0:19:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of our 'alliance',\N I'll allow you speak for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.96,0:19:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Since my defeat at Xu Province, I haven't heard of my brother's survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.27,0:19:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There are many in the world who look similar,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.57,0:19:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so how could that man with\N such traits happen to be Guan Yu?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.97,0:19:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, let's verify this, then decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.15,0:19:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see the man who killed Yan Liang?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.68,0:19:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.94,0:19:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I almost killed a decent man because of you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.85,0:19:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, me and General Yan were oathsworn!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.82,0:19:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I must avenge him!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.79,0:19:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me meet with the enemy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.76,0:19:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Only General Wen can avenge this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.73,0:20:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give you 100,000 men. Cross the Yellow River and hunt down that fiend!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.50,0:20:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,My lord, you must not!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.02,0:20:06.22,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(88,341)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,1850,2180)}Jǔ Shòu
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.20,0:20:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,We should remain at Yan ford and send a regiment towards Guandu afterwards.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.47,0:20:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If the situation goes awry when we \Ncross the river, it will be too late to return!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.94,0:20:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You burden the army with your talk. \NAnymore from you will delay us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.52,0:20:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Dispatch the men. We will leave immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.12,0:20:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.16,0:20:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Wen Chou is a famed \Ngeneral of Hebei. Who'll take him?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.65,0:20:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.12,0:20:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,En garde, Wen Chou!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.40,0:21:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you dare fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.55,0:21:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,En garde, knave!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.24,0:21:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guan is a true hero!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.34,0:21:20.22,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(604,341)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,1620,1860)}Zhāng Liáo\NStyled: Wényuǎn
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.76,0:21:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.71,0:21:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.29,0:21:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Second Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.10,0:21:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you hear someone call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.76,0:21:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.13,0:21:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Was someone calling to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.67,0:22:04.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Liu Bei, what is your excuse this time!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.84,0:22:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What did I do wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.79,0:22:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.80,0:22:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You had your brother kill a great general!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.60,0:22:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that without crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.47,0:22:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Take him out and behead him!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.12,0:22:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Wait! Let me have my final word!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.38,0:22:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}My lord. Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.20,0:22:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Cao Cao has gone after me with restlessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.16,0:22:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Now he's learned of me residing by thy side, fearing our alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.72,0:22:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Thus he had Yunchang kill the two generals,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.86,0:22:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}aimed to enrage you, sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.94,0:22:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}This is to have me be blamed by the nobles of Hebei,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.66,0:22:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}and thus twist thy hand to kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.02,0:23:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Nobles of Hebei,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.42,0:23:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}will not one of you implore for me to His Excellency?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.20,0:23:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Why have I been so forsaken?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.47,0:23:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.90,0:23:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande's words are correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.36,0:23:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You almost harmed my virtuous reputation!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.14,0:24:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no way of repaying \NYour Lordship's magnanimity!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.44,0:24:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I will send a trusted messenger to meet with Yunchang in secrecy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.71,0:24:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,so he'll have news of me; he'll rush through the night to join us.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.76,0:24:18.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,We'll assist you, sire, to execute that traitor,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.21,0:24:21.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,avenging Yan Liang and Wen Chou! What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.46,0:24:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If I can get Yunchang, he'll be worth more than\N ten Yan Liangs and Wen Chous combined!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.74,0:24:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.36,0:24:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us fetch brush and ink, and \Nwrite this down in front of everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.98,0:24:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guan!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.02,0:24:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.65,0:24:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,One of your old acquaintances.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.59,0:24:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him in.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.80,0:24:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.86,0:25:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guan!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.93,0:25:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, who are you, and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.70,0:25:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,why do you claim to be an acquaintance?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.58,0:25:08.46,Style Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(610,331)\fade(255,0,255,0,380,1620,1860)}Chén Zhèn\NStyled: Xiàoqǐ
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.41,0:25:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Yuan Shao's subordinate, \NChen Zhen of Nanyang.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.39,0:25:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,This here is Liu Bei's personal letter. \NGeneral Guan, please read.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.64,0:25:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"We made an oath in the Peach Garden,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.32,0:25:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"swearing we would die together."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.22,0:25:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"So why are we alive yet divided,\Nand with our bond and goal abandoned?"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.54,0:25:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"If you really covet glory and wealth,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.54,0:25:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"I will offer my head for you to achieve it."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.60,0:25:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"I have not said everything. \NI anxiously await your reply."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.25,0:26:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Elder Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.12,0:26:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,"It's not that I don't want to find you,"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.97,0:26:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,"but that I do not know where you are!"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.27,0:26:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,"Younger brother, how could you betray \Nour oath for wealth and glory?"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.82,0:26:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande hopes to see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.10,0:26:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do not want to betray your oath, \Nthen you should go see him now.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.50,0:27:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Men born within this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.00,0:27:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}without being consistent deserve no respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.90,0:27:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I came here openly and I must leave in the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.60,0:27:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I will write a letter and burden you to give the reply back.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.32,0:27:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}That once I leave Cao Cao,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.52,0:27:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}me and his two sister-in-laws will see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.69,0:27:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But if Cao Cao won't let you leave, what then?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.80,0:27:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I would rather accept death. \NHow could I remain here?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.00,0:27:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, you should write a reply to reassure Lord Liu.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.00,0:28:17.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Men who are righteous will not betray;\Nmen who are loyal do not fear death.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.98,0:28:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}When I was young, I studied such, and have a broad understanding of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.14,0:28:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Whenever I see the example of Yang Jueai and Zuo Botao,
Comment: 0,0:28:24.14,0:28:27.14,Note (Potential style?),,0,0,0,,Note recommended.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.64,0:28:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I have always sighed and wept.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.88,0:28:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}When I defended Xiapi, it did not have enough resources inside
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.38,0:28:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}or soldiers outside. I would have accepted death.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.20,0:28:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}However, knowing your love of your two wives,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.90,0:28:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I did not kill myself, or that would betray our trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.32,0:28:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}And so I allowed myself to be captured, planning to escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.10,0:28:57.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}And now knowing of your location,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.10,0:29:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I will bid farewell to Cao Cao and leave with your two wives.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.46,0:29:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Should I ever have evil thoughts, may the gods punish me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.74,0:29:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}For all our friendship, ink and paper hold every word.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.56,0:29:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I hope to see you in person. This is with all due respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.34,0:29:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I know my brother's heart and its unsaid questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.98,0:29:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,If there are complaints, I am willing to bear them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.38,0:29:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Wenyuan, what is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.08,0:29:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have heard you received news \Nof Xuande and came to congratulate you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.49,0:30:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Although my lord is here, I can't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.67,0:30:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why congratulate?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.91,0:30:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The relationship between you and Xuande...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.02,0:30:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,how does it compare to ours?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.12,0:30:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are good friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.83,0:30:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Xuande and I are both friends, and brothers most of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.77,0:30:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We are also lord and subject. \NHow could you compare the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.24,0:30:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now Xuande is at Hebei.\NSir, are you going there or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.65,0:31:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,How could I betray my promise?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.83,0:31:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wenyuan, you must see the Chancellor\Nto convey my will on my behalf.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.17,0:31:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Yunchang has decided?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.81,0:31:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A just man's words are to the point; \Nevery sentence flies true.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.15,0:31:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I should have never agreed to his terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.72,0:31:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, if not for your promise, how could Yunchang follow us?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.43,0:31:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If so...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.67,0:31:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting him go is really a pity,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.54,0:31:56.69,Default,,0,0,0,,but if you force Yunchang to stay, he will resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.98,0:32:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And that is my dilemma!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.05,0:32:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Wenyuan, you may leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.46,0:32:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.89,0:32:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a plan to keep him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.03,0:32:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.87,0:32:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I suppose Wenyuan told him my intentions,\Nfor the Chancellor avoids me.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.55,0:33:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Inform General Zhang that I have urgent matters to discuss!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.13,0:33:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,General Zhang is resting and will not receive any visitors.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.98,0:33:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask you, sir, to please tell the general that I want to see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.60,0:33:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but I am under specific orders from General Zhang.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.30,0:33:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,General Guan, you are no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.30,0:33:40.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.63,0:33:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.03,0:33:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Wenyuan, am I not a guest?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.62,0:33:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you use sleep \Nas an excuse to reject my visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.92,0:34:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you won't see me, I will \Ngo see the Chancellor again!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.68,0:34:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, sorry for the bother. \NWhy won't the Chancellor see guests?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.66,0:34:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm only a servant within the house. \NI know nothing of the Chancellor's affairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.10,0:34:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You know nothing?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.73,0:35:01.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Indeed I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.52,0:35:08.27,Default,,0,0,0,,My wish to leave is set. How could I stay?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.96,0:35:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.90,0:35:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.70,0:35:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you checked carefully?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.16,0:35:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,By your orders, I wouldn't dare make a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.44,0:35:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.22,0:35:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Then please tell me the Chancellor's gifts
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.31,0:35:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,have all been left here,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.67,0:36:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they must not be touched.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.28,0:36:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.49,0:36:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Only...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.72,0:36:13.33,Default,,0,0,0,,General.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.24,0:36:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}This seal was granted to you by the court.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.12,0:36:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}General, I think you should keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.66,0:37:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}This seal is the Chancellor's doing. Leave it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.24,0:37:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,General!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.24,0:37:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"I have learned that my former master is with Yuan Shao."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.44,0:37:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"With our previous oath, how could I ever betray it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.24,0:37:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"Despite your generosity, my master's cause is more important."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.24,0:37:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"I have left a special message,\N written with the most respect."
Comment: 0,0:37:38.24,0:37:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Above line needs to be reviewed: 茲特奉書告辭，伏惟照察. Could also be  "which will explain everything".
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.24,0:37:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}"I still have not yet fully paid your kindness, and I hope to do so one day."
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.80,0:37:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Reporting to the Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.75,0:37:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Guan Yu has locked away all the gifted gold and silver,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.42,0:38:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,the ten beauties are housed in a separate room,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.02,0:38:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the noble seal of Hanshou has been hung up at the hall,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.02,0:38:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and the men you assigned have all been left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.15,0:38:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He only took his own followers and luggage, and left from the North Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.70,0:38:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.67,0:38:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I can take 3,000 cavalry to go capture \NGuan Yu and deliver him to you, Chancellor!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.00,0:38:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Chancellor, why not give the order?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.15,0:38:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Never forgetting his roots, coming and \Nleaving so cleanly. What a true man!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.63,0:38:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You all should follow his example.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.00,0:38:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you really letting him go?!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.34,0:39:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody, back down!\NDo not speak of this again!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.72,0:39:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}You have treated Guan Yu extraordinarily well,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.72,0:39:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}yet he left without even a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.80,0:39:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}This was an act to humiliate you and it should be avenged.
Comment: 0,0:39:43.66,0:39:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Rewording recommended for the above.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.09,0:39:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Now if you let him join Yuan Shao,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.60,0:39:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}it is no different than adding wings to a tiger!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.80,0:39:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}If you don't hunt him down, he'll cause trouble later!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.20,0:39:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Absolutely not.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.50,0:39:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}I made a promise with him, so I cannot break it!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.66,0:39:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}As your lord, do not chase him!
Comment: 0,0:39:43.66,0:39:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Rewording recommended for the above 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.46,0:39:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Wenyuan.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.84,0:39:56.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.34,0:39:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Yunchang has abandoned his seal and the gold.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.14,0:40:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Riches could not sway his loyalty;
Comment: 0,0:40:02.99,0:41:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Audio stops here.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.32,0:40:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}titles could not stir his ambitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.34,0:40:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Such men have my utmost respect!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.24,0:40:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}He won't have gone far. I will do him one last favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.38,0:40:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Wenyuan, have Yunchang wait for a moment to await my escort.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.42,0:40:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Gift him a warrior's cloak and passage for the journey.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.72,0:40:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(352,429)}Let this be our parting memory.
